<subSubSection id="C33D698DD850FFC4BF96E6A62DB6FD31" pageId="68" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B983A06D850FFC4BF96E6A62DB6FD31" blockId="68.[192,1440,707,763]" pageId="68" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B953E614D850FFC4BF96E6A62952FD11" bold="true" box="[192,324,707,731]" pageId="68" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is recognized by the blue elytron contrasted to yellowish red pronotum, densely, fairly coarsely punctured dorsal surface, and produced, widely emarginate anterior margin of prosternum.
</paragraph>
